76561198036301755,Not Recommended,212160,30085604,Posted: 21 February,all,416,"I've been playing this game since 2011 and continue to play it today (casually). It's important to keep that in mind throughout the rest of the review since I'll be wording things from a Casual player's perspective.THE GOOD• Great, shiny graphics (but due to its age, don't expect to be blown away).• Very solid, satisfying melee combat, second to none that I've seen. You can almost feel each hit, each slice, each stab.• The characters are numerous and play differently, making for great replayability.• Raids are so much funTHE BAD• Graphics can be overproduced at times, leading so slow performance even with a good PC• Lower-level quests are mind-numbingly dull with the same trash mobs over and over, in the same rooms over and over (only in lower levels)• The story content  is not worth the amount of time you'll spend walking back and forth in town between NPCs (only in lower levels)• player base seems to be shrinking at an alarming rate. Only Veterans seem to log in anymoreTHE IMPORTANT NOTEThe next fact is neither Good nor Bad: There is a large range between Casual and Veteran players. This is understandable; Casuals don't want to put in all the time to get the best gear, and Veterans do not want to Raid with dead-weight. For the latest and most stat-heavy content, you will likely not be welcomed onto a Veteran boat if you are not a Veteran. However, Veterans are more than happy to Raid with you on older content.Nexon has made many improvements to the game since I started playing. Story-based drops are now guaranteed, you can purchase rare materials with Seals (gained over time doing Raids) and different difficulties are available for each Raid to tailor to your skill level and equipment. Content-wise, the game is at it's best right now.However, since the Steam Recommendation is based on whether or not I'd suggest it to new players, the answer is No. The lower-level grind is too dull, and the small player base may be indicative of a Conclusion sometime soon.That being said, I'll continue to play it as a filthy Casual. :)"
